Pretty abysmal service for average food.

I was looking forward to trying this place and ended up really disappointed with the experience. I think the waitress kept forgetting about us, and our service was unbelievably slow. She took orders from several tables who were seated after us before taking ours. Some of these tables were done eating before our food even arrived. If the food was amazing, I would have gotten over it. But the food was pretty average. I don't plan to return.

Green Chilaquiles were not at my expectations $14 over priced. Chorizo more like sausage patty. MAC & CHESEE WAS BLAND. Taste like rubbery the cheese was at my dislike . Sandwich over-all (Avocado Smashed) was delicious. Atmosphere was nice. However the food wise needs more flavor.

Popularity overruled the flavor of the food. I couldn't eat my steak it was so so hard. The food lacked seasoning, bland. Especially for the price. Customer service is a plus. They've gotten away from taste quality
Nice facility, great menu, great staff, wonderful owners.

The pancakes..OMG.  There might be a person out there who has had Cafe Bellagio pancakes before they closed Cafe Bellagio in the Bellagio hotel Vegas.  And if you have you will know what a GREAT pancake should taste like.  RIP Cafe Bellagio but here in my own backyard is this wonderfulness!!!  Sausage and Bacon accompany is good as well.  Syrup...Perfectly paired on the pancakes of my dreams.

Great breakfast and service in a good location of Chicago. If you go to the south corner and go east you will reach downtown in a short period of time. It is worth the visit.  Reminds new of Baby Stacks. Just alot bigger and a healthier menu
Delicious omelette and my husband had the BLT which was really good as well. Had to have a cup of orange/strawberry juice to go too!

The waitress was very welcoming and knowledgeable of the menu! She gave us amazing recommendations based on what kind of tastes we prefer!  I wish I remembered her name because it was some of the best service I have had. I also like how they allow people to use their cafe as a study spot if they are not busy. Not only is the service/people amazing but the food and coffee are excellent! Definitely will be back in future.
Second time here and they do not disappoint. I love the pot-roast Benedict.
Patio is the perfect place for a calm brunch. Staff was great!
Food was all incredible!! Get the cinnamon roll waffles to share for the table, you won't regret it.
Great service and food is always really good at both locations! The server recommended these mini breakfast tacos and I was happy I listened to her!

We have been going to Stax for years and not once had a bad meal or service. The food is incredible! Spiro makes sure to treat his customers like family. He always remembers us and takes time to say hi.

WOW! Came here with my friend for Valentine's and the food was delicious. Today I decided to order for take out & it was ready on time, and the whole pickup set up was perfect. When I came back into my office, I noticed they tossed in two extra little pancakes for free! That really brightened my day :) If you're looking for a breakfast spot with awesome food for reasonable prices, this is your spot!
Fantastic service, great food and very very clean.
Found my new favorite breakfast place! They are super accommodating and the food is amazing. And the pricing is super reasonable. Love it

Ordered via uber eats.. received a quick delivery and a free pancake. Appreciate y'all during this time, please know your work does not go unnoticed. I dont even write reviews but definitely had to for this experience.

The hosted that was on duty today either has a attitude problem or she's just ignorant. I spoke to her and she just stood there looking at me, when leaving, I told her to have a good day and this woman turned her back and walked away. The food is consistently good here. I love enjoying a late breakfast. I don’t recommend going near closing time because they start cleaning and the smell of cleaning products can ruin your breakfast.
Bring back the parma prosciutto!!!!!!!!
This place has become a Sunday tradition. Great food, great service. Every time.
Overpriced food. My boyfriend didn't like his food and service was average.
Great food
Great service, good place and friendly staff , children are allowed , good food quality and quantity.. everything was delicious and I highly recommend the white chocolate raspberry pancakes

I’m obsessed with their carrot, orange juice they have, while my friend ordered eggs and potatoes and the waffle stack I had the French toast with dolce de leche and bananas omg it was amazing!!! Like I’ve said in my other reviews., I can’t wait to go back to Chicago just eat here all over again.

I started my meal with a side of mini pancakes, which was two large pancakes. They had a fluffy yet slightly dense, cake like texture/flavor, likely from the sugary batter. I prefer a slightly thinner consistency to my maple syrup but the flavor was good nonetheless. My main dish was the hot ham ‘n cheese crepes. They came topped with an arugula salad, drizzled with honey mustard having a glaze like consistency. The sweet and savory flavors complimented each other nicely. My husband had the meat wagon omelet which was loaded with a combination of meats to which he added cheddar cheese. The meat was all high quality with great flavor. He had the house potatos on the side which could have used seasoning as it was not flavorful like the rest of our food. The portion sizes were all large we took home plenty of leftovers. I always appreciate when the waitstaff keeps my water glass and coffee cup full, which they did. I would definitely recommend Stax to anyone looking for a high quality, unique breakfast while in Chicago.
I have dreamt about the lemon blueberry pancakes... 🤤 Love coming here!
Good food, very slow service
Food is great and affordable and the service is nice would recommend
It’s a comfortable place, the light is warm, lots of options of food.

The food is so good! There is a ton of options, and it comes out fast! Their staff is amazing and well trained. I had a chance of meeting the store owners of the family business and they are great people I would want to have breakfast with🥞
Great environment ,amazing staff and delicious food 😍
Great service and food! Our waiter Rocky was awesome!
The kind of menu you could throw a dart at (everything is great!)
Looks ok, but walked out after 10 minutes while the coffee was "brewing"
Some of the best food I have ever consumed.
Brunch was great, service was great and it was very reasonable on the wallet!! I will definitely go again. This location also has a small alcohol beverage menu and their Bellini was fabulous!!

Great breakfast place whether you want sweet or savory! I used to go to the Taylor street location by UIC all the time. So happy this one opened up. I love the outdoor patio too! Maybe because it's a newer location or whatever the reason but there usually is no wait for the patio! An added bonus among the many the restaurants we frequent along the Milwaukee Street bike corridor.

Great neighborhood spot. We went early and had the place to ourselves. Menu is a little overwhelming but the food is divine - you can't go wrong.

Great food.  I'll be back.

Great food and beautifully presented. Ate breakfast there 3 times during our visit to Chicago and would have been there every day if we had found it earlier in our stay. Service was a little shakey one day but chalked it up to an inexperienced server.  Would highly recommend Stax.
Everything on the menu is delicious. Excellent service
i made love to the cinnamon roll waffle and monte carlo waffle

I was finally able to try the new Stax location! The service at these restaurants is always great. The coffee is yummy too. Their special for the day were lavender lemon pancakes- YUM! I always love a good skillet too. Look at how pretty those over-easy eggs are!!

Service was ok Food was almost tasteless Coffee was not good Ordered iced coffee which tasted like water Was not busy around 1pm They have TV's which would be better if they showed sports especially during playoff season

good food roomy clean nice service

My absolute favorite breakfast spot! We travel from the burbs for their food! Their menu is on trend , yet comfortable and always fresh and delicious! And if you are like me, atmosphere and the visual ambiance of a location makes a huge difference too. Innovatively designed- modern industrial,  meets color, meets farmhouse details- a perfect mix! The owner always stops by our table and personally asks us how everything was- no small feat on a hugely busy Sunday morning!! It’s our go to- if you haven’t been you are missing out!!
Best breakfast in the area. If that wasn't enough, the service is stellar. Can get busy but you'd never know it by how well the place is run. Mini waffles, and lumberjack skillet well worth the $.

Great breakfast spot where there aren't too many places to go.  Steak and Eggs, healthy oatmeal pancakes were both really good. Server very friendly but kitchen backed up bad on a Sunday morning.

Breakfast was fantastic. Service was great as well. I ordered an omelette and all of the ingredients tasted fresh. The house potatoes and mini pancakes(which were regular size) that came with it were good as well. My husband had banana french toast topped with dulce de leche. The only negative thing I will say is that the portions were HUGE! We wasted so much food which seems sad and unnecessary.

There were boxes and restaurant materials. Employees came to complain to each other right next to our booth. It felt we were forgotten about. We won't return. The food is decent.

Slow(er) service- place was only 1/3 full when we arrived and maybe 2/3 full by the time we left and everything still felt like it took too long. I'll definitely be coming back  Edit: was too full when writing the review and forgot to mention that the food comes out steaming hot and fresh but also the staff is very attentive which is way better than that terrible spot in Wrigley called Kanela.

Not good, overpriced and bad service. Waiter was MIA half the time, didn't check on us, barely refilled our drinks & forgot to bring us pitchers when asked several times. Also, food was cold, overcooked and not all food was brought out bc waiter forgot to add it to the order. Management didn't even come around to see how everything was nor apologize for the delay..
Delicious breakfast!

Great food and very well cooked! Definitely a great fast casual breakfast spot.  Would give this 5 stars except the mimosas cost more than food... which isn’t even fresh squeezed oj (poured out of a container).

I went here for their soft opening and went back the next day for their grand opening in order to make a fair review.  I am a big fan of their food, they really know how to do breakfast right.  There are so many choices that, you can come here many times and get something every time, and each time will be just as delicious as the last.  We had the braised beef brisket benedict (sauteed with celery, carrots, & onions, with poached eggs & hollandaise sauce on an english muffin) with house potatoes, and the half pound angus burger (with lettuce, tomato, onion, pepper bacon, cheddar & tomato jam) with a side of fries on the first day.  The braised beef brisket benedict was the favorite, and the half pound angus burger was a close 2nd.  On the second day, we had the prosciutto avocado benedict (two poached eggs & hollandaise sauce on an english muffin) with house potatoe,s and the meat wagon (chorizo, fire roasted tomatoes, poblano, queso fresco, topped with pico de gallo & chipotle.  Both entrees are very popular and are served with house potatoes.  Both are really good, again the prosciutto avocado benedict was the favorite.  Try the strawberry and orange juice, it's almost too pretty to drink!  Really loved the decor, it's a modern, bright, open space with an outdoor patio.  I would've given this restaurant 5 stars, except for one exception.  When we sat down on their opening day, I turned my coffee mug around and it had lipstick on it!  It was there before I got there.  This was within the first hour on the first day that they were open to the public.  Our waiter changed my coffee mug for me, but, this is not something I would expect from any restaurant, let alone a new one.
Visited Stax today on their opening day! Beautiful funky atmosphere with delicious food options for everyone, family friendly, and great service-will be back for sure!!
